beer.beer_description: American style pale ale, dark gold in colour with a delicate white head. Citrus and floral aromas lead into hop flavours characterised by grapefruit and mandarin produced. A dry bitter finish makes this an eminently enjoyable beer.

Spring/Summer seasonal A pale amber beer, hopped exclusively with lots of New Zealand varieties. An antipodean extravaganza, lightly carbonated with a soft bitterness from a combination of Southern Cross and Pacifica, leading into tropical fruit flavours of pineapple and mango, with the wonderful addition of grapes from Nelson Sauvin hops – a delightful spring beer!

So good. Had to get another.

items.badge_description: It takes the perfect amount light, the right framing and a touch of creative love to get the perfect picture of your brew. Now it’s time to drink it! That’s 5 check-ins with a photo.

items.checkin_comment: Aaahh. So good and so refreshing. Light hops and hints of fruit.

items.badge_description: Does the word picking favorites mean anything to you? Obviously not. That's 10 different beers in a row.
You've discovered a pot of gold, or you've just had one too many. That's at least 5 Irish beers. Try 5 more for Level 2.
